PROCEDURE:  SYS3.SYSTEM.DOCLIB#SYSHIPL
REVISED:    02/08/99
AUTHOR:     Kusum Kumar

                   SYSH  IPL Procedure

Follow these steps for a simple ipl of SYSH in current date of 1998.
If you plan on IPL'ing SYSH into a future  date,  use  procedure  in
SYS3.SYSTEM.DOCLIB#HALIPL.   This  procedure  has  more  detail  for
system shutdown and IPL.


   Steps:                               Action:

0. For an IPL in current date, AUTOSUBP does not require purging.
   When IPL'ing into a future century, it will.  See instructions
   noted in SYS3.SYSTEM.DOCLIB#HALIPL.

1. Enter System Date or GMT time         ----> R 00,DATE=YYYY.DDD,
                                               CLOCK=HH.MM.SS,GMT
      (Enter system date as specified on ipl scheduled, reply u if
        current)

2. IEA903A REPLY "U" WHEN THE ENTERED TIME OCCURS
                                          ----> R 00,U

3. *01 IEE357A REPLY WITH SMF VALUES OR U ----> R 01,U

4. *02 IEE956A REPLY - FTIME=HH.MM.SS,NAME=OPERATOR,REASON=(IPL
   REASON) OR U                          ----> R 02,U

5. *03 $HASP426 SPECIFY OPTIONS - JES2 SP 3.1.3
                                         ----> R 03,U

6. *$HASP493 JES2 ALL SYSTEMS WARM START IS IN PROGRESS
    $HASP400 ENTER REQUESTS              ----> $S

7. *04 ERB306D ZZ : REPLY WITH OPTIONS OR GO
                                         ---->  R 04,GO

8. Start Interactives                    ----> S HAWK
                                         Console message:
                                         $HASP373 ATLMS STARTED

9. Vary tape drives                    ----> V (XXX-XXX),ONLINE

                                        Tape drives come up offline
                                        at IPL. For system ipled,
                                        check to be certain tape
                                        drives to be varied online
                                        are offline for all other
                                        systems

10. Open front ends and clear any      ----> @START ALL
    outstanding message                ----> @SET MSG

                                        (Clears any system msg. from
                                         previous ipl)

11. Release the queue                   ----> $AQ,ALL
